dcterms:description: A collection of benchmark problem sets that includes a total of 108 satisfiable and unsatisfiable instances with underlying graphs, used to demonstrate the effectiveness of vertex elimination based methods for acyclicity and reachability checking.
dcterms:title: Benchmark problem sets

dcterms:description: A dataset used for checking the existence of Hamiltonian cycles in two-dimensional grids, which can be encoded into formulas with underlying graphs and the constraint of acyclicity.
dcterms:title: Hamiltonian cycles in two-dimensional grids
